FBIS3-49553 "dreeu008_h_94006" FBIS-EEU-94-008 Document Type:Daily Report 12 Jan 1994 HUNGARY Border Guard Seeks Armored Vehicles From China LD1001155894 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 1400 GMT 10 Jan 94 LD1001155894 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network Language: Hungarian Article Type:BFN [Text] The border guard wishes to obtain at least 100 armored carriers from China in exchange for China's state debts. The vehicles would be given to the 19 border patrol companies. The Nikex joint stock company, which has been commissioned by the Ministry of the Interior to conclude the deal, announced that a Hungarian delegation is to travel to Beijing in the next few days in order to gather information. China owes Hungary over seven billion forints.
